# BrickCode — Supabase client config (Task B1/B2)
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. For LOCAL development, `supabase start`
# prints the API URL and the anon key — use those.
#
# SECURITY: only the *anon* (public) key belongs here. It is safe to expose
# because Row Level Security + the submit_session RPC are the real guardrails.
# NEVER put the service_role key in the frontend, in .env files that ship, or
# in any committed doc — it bypasses RLS.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Class code the simulator submits sessions under. DEV FALLBACK only — the app
# has an in-product "Unirse a una clase" screen that stores the code in
# localStorage and takes precedence over this. If both are unset, sessions still
# record locally but won't sync. See docs/hosting.md.
VITE_CLASS_CODE=
